AB  - Accurate identification of druggable pockets and their features is essential for 
      structure-based drug design and effective downstream docking. Here, we present 
      RAPID-Net, a deep learning-based algorithm designed for the accurate prediction 
      of binding pockets and seamless integration with docking pipelines. On the 
      PoseBusters benchmark, RAPID-Net-guided AutoDock Vina achieves 54.9% of Top-1 
      poses with RMSD < 2 A and satisfying the PoseBusters chemical-validity criterion, 
